gomodel:SYNGO_3998  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Constitutively active Rab17(Q77L) is preferentially localised to dendrites of hippocampal neurons. RABGEF1 was identified as a GEF of Rab17 in a Y2H screen. Like Rab17(Q77L), overexpression of RABGEF1 increases localisation of Rab17 in dendrites (not axons). In comparison, the inactive RABGEF1 mutant (D313A) had no effect on redistribution of Rab17.\n\nAdditionally, RABGEF1 also enhances localisation of Rab5A and Rab21 into dendrites and axons. RABGEF1, together with Rab5 and Rab17, regulates the development of axons and dendrites in hippocampal neurons.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods: \"cDNAs encoding mouse Rabex-5 (aa 1-491), Rabex-5-C (aa 208-491), ALS2 (aa 1-1651), and ALS2-C (aa 1485-1651) were similarly produced by conventional PCR techniques (see Fig. 1D). A Rabex-5 mutant carrying an Asp-to-Ala mutation at amino acid positions 313 (D313A) and an ALS2 mutant (D1593A) were prepared by using conventional PCR techniques and mutagenic\noligonucleotides as described previously.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2020-08-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3998" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

